Cursor-Specific Project Rules:

Follow PEP8 standards for all Python code

Document each function with a clear docstring describing its purpose, inputs, and outputs

Use Git for version control, and regularly commit changes

Run linting (e.g., flake8) on the code to ensure it’s clean and follows standards

Write unit tests for all critical functions (strategy logic, risk management, execution)

Use a .env file for securely storing API keys and avoid exposing them in the code

Implement error handling for common issues like API errors, high volatility, and connection issues

Paper trade for at least 100 simulated trades before live trading

Trading Bot Development Workflow

Development workflow must always follow:

Cursor → GitHub → VPS

The VPS runs the production bot and must never be modified directly.

All code changes must follow this process:

Modify code locally in Cursor

Ensure changes do not alter strategy logic unless explicitly requested

Commit changes to Git

Push to GitHub

Deploy to VPS using:

git pull
sudo systemctl restart tradingbot

Direct editing of code on the VPS is prohibited except for emergency debugging.

Production Safety Rules

The following modules control live trading behavior and must not be modified unless explicitly requested:

strategy.py
risk.py
execution.py

Safe modules to modify:

notifications.py
journal.py
equity.py
scanner.py
main.py (only orchestration logic)
Risk Management Constraints

The assistant must preserve the following system constraints:

Risk per trade = 1%
Daily loss limit = 3%
Max portfolio exposure = 50%

These values must never be removed or overridden.

Logging Requirements

All new features must log useful data.

Logs must be written to:

logs/

Required files:

trading_bot_YYYYMMDD.log
equity_curve.csv
Monitoring Rules

Telegram notifications must exist for:

bot start
trade entry
trade exit
errors
4-hour status reports

Status messages must not be sent more frequently than every 4 hours.

When proposing major architecture changes (e.g. scanners, exchanges, new risk logic),
the assistant must first describe the plan before modifying the code.

Research Strategy Development Rules

New experimental strategies must be developed in a separate research environment.

Do not modify the production trading bot when developing new strategies.

Research code must be placed in:

research/
strategies/

Production modules that must not be modified:

strategy.py
risk.py
execution.py
main.py

Research strategies must be implemented as standalone backtesting scripts first.

Only after a research strategy is validated may integration into the production engine be proposed.